  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Finance Executive",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p><strong>Accounting & Financial Reporting</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain full set of accounts, including General Ledger, Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, Fixed Assets and Bank Reconciliations</p></li><li><p>Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports</p></li><li><p>Ensure accurate recording of all financial transactions in accordance with accounting standards</p></li><li><p>Perform reconciliation balance sheet accounts and preparation of balance sheet schedules</p></li><li><p>Assist in month-end and year-end closing activities</p></li></ul><p><strong>GST & Tax Compliance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare and submit GST returns accurately and on time.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with GST regulations and statutory requirements</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation and records for tax and audit purposes</p></li><li><p>Liaise with auditors, IRAS, and relevant authorities when required</p></li></ul><p><strong>Operational Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Process invoices, payments, and receipts</p></li><li><p>Monitor cash flow and follow up on outstanding receivables</p></li><li><p>Support budgeting and forecasting exercises</p></li><li><p>Assist in internal controls and process improvements</p></li></ul><p><strong>Administrative & Audit Support</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare schedules and documents for external audits</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper filing and record-keeping of accounting documents</p></li><li><p>Perform other accounting or finance-related duties as assigned</p></li><li><p>Perform any ad-hoc tasks assigned by the superior<br /></p></li></ul><h2> <strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related discipline</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1–2 years of relevant accounting experience, including preparation of a full set of accounts</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience in GST preparation and submission</p></li><li><p>Good understanding of accounting principles and local tax regulations</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail and accuracy</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and meet deadlines</p></li><li><p>Experience in handling audits and liaising with auditors</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li></ul>",
